  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to determine the effects of the addition of insulin glargine
      during the early phase of moderate to severe Diabetic Ketoacidosis (DKA) in children.

      The investigators hypothesize that the addition of insulin glargine during the early phase of
      management of DKA will accelerate acidosis correction, decrease the length of insulin
      infusion, and decrease the total intensive care unit time in children admitted to the ICU.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
