  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Ages 6-18 y.o. presenting to Vanderbilt Children's Hospital (VCH) Emergency Room with:

          -  Established history of insulin dependent diabetes

        AND:

          -  Chief c/o hyperglycemia or vomiting

          -  Venous pH &lt; 7.24

          -  Serum Bicarbonate &lt; 18

          -  Blood glucose &gt; 150

          -  Urinary Ketones

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Age &lt; 6y.o.

          -  New onset diabetes

          -  Received IV insulin bolus prior to arrival to VCH Emergency Room (ER)

          -  Venous pH &gt; 7.24

          -  Serum Bicarbonate &gt; 18

          -  Pregnancy

          -  Received glargine within 12 hours prior to arrival to VCH Emergency Room/Pediatric
             Critical Care Unit
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
